post_text:
Crews worked hard this summer to accomplish the many projects that needed to be completed prior to the start of school.
Summer Activities
- Blue gym was demolished to allow for the installation of the new stadium. The demolition was completed in the beginning of August.
- The South Rolling Road expansion project was completed by the end of August. Portions of South Rolling Road will now allow for pedestrian traffic and parallel parking on both sides of the street.
- The rework of Speakman Drive was completed. Speakman Drive was reopened for student traffic by the beginning of the school year.
The building continues to make progress. The primary focus this Fall, is to complete the roof installation and installing the windows throughout the building. The goal is to have the building weather-tight by end of December. Work crews will continue to work on the installation of the stadium throughout the fall and winter months.

The building continues to make progress. The primary focus this Fall, is to complete the roof installation and installing the windows throughout the building. The goal is to have the building weather-tight by end of December. Work crews will continue to work on the installation of the stadium throughout the fall and winter months.

post_text:
Last evening, the Springfield School District presented its Master Plan design to the Springfield Planning Commission. The Planning Commission acts in an advisory role to the Township Commissioners. We were pleased with the open dialogue from Springfield residents, as this is part of the process when building a new school.

The Planning Commission chose to recommend denial of the plan as presented and voiced specific concerns with height and location of the new building and traffic patterns.

Please note that the Springfield School District is committed to building a new high school and will thoughtfully consider the Commission’s information while remaining focused on all stakeholders in this process.

post_text: UPDATE: By mutual agreement of Springfield Township and the Springfield School District, the Township Planning Commission’s Review of the preliminary land development plans for the proposed new Springfield High School is being postponed from October 6, 2016, to a date yet to be determined, in order to give the technical experts and attorneys the opportunity to review and discuss the Township Staff’s review comments and the District’s preliminary responses in order to better understand and to attempt to resolve as many of the issues as possible and to narrow those issues requiring further study and discussion at the Planning Commission Meeting.

post_text:
On November 4, Springfield School District sold the initial piece of new debt related to the high school master plan, the 2015 Series bond issue in the amount of $9,995,000. The bonds are expected to close in December 2015. The term runs until 2043, with an average rate of 3.39%.

Compared to original projections, this is anticipated to yield a savings of $850,000 in future interest costs, as the average blended rate for the issue was originally projected at 4.2%, and realized at 3.39%.
